 "cells": [

   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# System Identification with the ``ssid`` package"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "from utilities.printing import *\n",
    "from utilities.testing import test_method\n",
    "from utilities.config import Config\n",
    "import ssid\n",
    "from ssid import modes\n",
    "from control.matlab import ss, lsim"
   ]
  },
  {
   "attachments": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Define a SDOF system\n",
    "parameter | value\n",
    "----------|-------\n",
    "m  | mass\n",
    "k  | stiffness\n",
    "c  | damping coefficient\n",
    "nt | number of timesteps\n",
    "dt | timestep"
   ]
  },
  {
   "attachments": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "![sdof](./figures/sdof.png)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "natural period: 1.1471s\n",
      "damping ratio: 0.01\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# parameters of SDOF system\n",
    "mass = 1       # mass\n",
    "k = 30         # stiffness\n",
    "zeta = 0.01    # damping ratio\n",
    "omega_n = np.sqrt(k/mass)  # natural frequency (rad/s)\n",
    "Tn = 2*np.pi/omega_n  # natural periods (s)\n",
    "c = 2*zeta*mass*omega_n    # damping coefficient\n",
    "print(f\"natural period: {Tn:<3.5}s\")\n",
    "print(f\"damping ratio: {zeta}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# forcing frequencies (rad/s)\n",
    "omega_f = [0.017*omega_n, 0.14*omega_n, 0.3*omega_n]"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# forcing function (input)\n",
    "nt = 5000       # number of timesteps\n",
    "dt = 0.03       # timestep\n",
    "tf = nt*dt      # final time\n",
    "t = np.arange(start = 0, stop = tf, step = dt)\n",
    "f = np.sum(np.sin([omega*t for omega in omega_f]), axis=0)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# displacement response (analytical solution) (output)\n",
    "omega_D = omega_n*np.sqrt(1-zeta**2)\n",
    "y = np.zeros((3,nt))\n",
    "for i,omega in enumerate(omega_f):\n",
    "    C3 = (1/k)*(1-(omega/omega_n)**2)/((1-(omega/omega_n)**2)**2+(2*zeta*omega/omega_n))**2\n",
    "    C4 = -(2*zeta*omega/omega_n)*(1-(omega/omega_n)**2)/((1-(omega/omega_n)**2)**2+(2*zeta*omega/omega_n))**2\n",
    "    C1 = -C4\n",
    "    C2 = (zeta*omega_n*C1-omega*C3)/omega_D\n",
    "    y[i,:] = np.exp(-zeta*omega_n*t)*(C1*np.cos(omega_D*t)+C2*np.sin(omega_D*t)) + C3*np.sin(omega*t) + C4*np.cos(omega*t)\n",
    "y = np.sum(y,axis=0)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 864x288 with 2 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# plot input vs. output\n",
    "plot_io(input=f, output=y, t=t, title=\"SDOF Displacement Response to Sinusoidal Forcing\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "attachments": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Perform System Identification"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 15,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "<class 'tuple'>\n",
      "Spectral quantities:\n",
      "         T                   T % error     % error\n",
      "      1.147      0.01         -2.323e-13    5.208e-11\n",
      "      2.9        0.8643       152.8        8.543e+03\n",
      "      0.05512    0.8956       -95.2        8.856e+03\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Generate a state space realization of the system\n",
    "A,B,C,D = ssid.system(input=f, output=y)\n",
    "# Obtain natural period and damping ratio from the state space model\n",
    "ss_modes = modes.modes((A,B,C,D),dt)\n",
    "print_modes(ss_modes, Tn=Tn, zeta=zeta)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 576x288 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Reproduce the response with the state space model\n",
    "y_ssid = lsim(ss(A,B,C,D,dt),f,t)[0]\n",
    "plot_pred(ytrue=y, models=y_ssid, t=t, title=\"System ID Predicted Displacement Response\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "attachments": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Breakdown of System Identification Methods"
   ]
  },
  {
   "attachments": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### General Parameters\n",
    "parameter | value\n",
    "----------|-------\n",
    "`p ` | number of output channels\n",
    "`q ` | number of input channels\n",
    "`nt` | number of timesteps\n",
    "`dt` | timestep\n",
    "\n",
    "### Specific to Observer Kalman Identification (OKID)\n",
    "parameter | value\n",
    "----------|-------\n",
    "`m`  | number of Markov parameters to compute (at most = nt)\n",
    "\n",
    "### Specific to Eigensystem Realization Algorithm (ERA)\n",
    "parameter | value\n",
    "----------|-------\n",
    "`no` | number of observability parameters\n",
    "`nc` | number of controllability parameters\n",
    "`r ` | reduced model order\n",
    "\n",
    "### Specific to Data Correlations (DC)\n",
    "parameter | value\n",
    "----------|-------\n",
    "`a`  | (alpha) number of additional block rows in Hankel matrix of correlation matrices\n",
    "`b`  | (beta) number of additional block columns in Hankel matrix of correlation matrices\n",
    "`l`  | initial lag\n",
    "`g`  | lag (gap) between correlations\n",
    "\n",
    "### Specific to System Realization with Information Matrix (SRIM)\n",
    "parameter | value\n",
    "----------|-------\n",
    "`no` | number of steps used for identification (prediction horizon)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "attachments": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Method Inputs"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Set parameters\n",
    "conf = Config()\n",
    "conf.m  = 300\n",
    "conf.no = 140\n",
    "conf.nc = 140\n",
    "conf.r  =   2\n",
    "conf.a  =   0\n",
    "conf.b  =   0\n",
    "conf.l  =  10\n",
    "conf.g  =   3\n",
    "\n",
    "# A place to store models and their predictions\n",
    "models = {}"
   ]
  },
  {
   "attachments": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### OKID-ERA"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 9,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Spectral quantities:\n",
      "         T                   T % error     % error\n",
      "      1.147      0.01043      0.01875      4.329    \n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# OKID-ERA\n",
    "method = \"okid-era\"\n",
    "models[method] = test_method(method=method, input=f, output=y, dt=dt, t=t, **conf)\n",
    "print_modes(models[method][\"modes\"], Tn=Tn, zeta=zeta)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "attachments": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [

  },
